OL,3,CBritish father-to-be feels like
OL,4,C'second class citizen' over family
OL,5,Cvisa rules
OL,7,FA British father-to-be who is feeling
OL,8,F"completely helpless" over the UK's
OL,9,Ffamily visa rules has said it feels
OL,10,Flike being "second-class citizens" for
OL,11,Ffalling in love with someone not from
OL,12,Fthe UK.
OL,14,FDavid Todd, 33, is calling on the
OL,15,FGovernment to reform the policy,
OL,16,Fincluding to scrap or lower the
OL,17,Fminimum income requirement (MIR) for
OL,18,FBritish citizens to bring their
OL,19,Fpartners to the country, as ministers
OL,20,Fmull over updating the visa route.
