OL,4,C'second class citizen' over family
OL,5,Cvisa rules
OL,7,F"It's this feeling that you're kind of
OL,8,Fhelpless, you're stuck in limbo, and
OL,9,Fyou're desperately trying to contort
OL,10,Fyourself into this position where you
OL,11,Fcan make it work just because you want
OL,12,Fto live with your wife or husband."
OL,14,FThe couple, living in Wurzburg,
OL,15,FGermany, first left the UK after Ms
OL,16,FTodd's student visa ended and moved to
OL,17,Fthe European nation so they could be
OL,18,Ftogether seven years ago.
